_:Nf83cffa7b6c94678a99353404ad963a1 <http://schema.org/description> "The Crown Estate is an independent commercial business, created by an Act of Parliament, with a diverse portfolio of UK buildings, shoreline, seabed, forestry, agriculture and common land. The business generates valuable revenue for the government and over the last 10 years has contributed £4.1 billion to the Consolidated Fund. The Crown Estate works with HM Treasury ." .
